During the course the articulation features and the articulation of Estonian speech sounds is taught, as well as their acoustics, speech prosody, and the phonological system of Estonian. Students (except students of Special Eduacation) get also to know and to use the Finno-Ugric phonetic transcription.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to get an overview of main terms and problems of Estonian phonetics and phonology, and also of main theoretical viewpoints and research methods.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Student knows the Estonian sound system and can give examples of different pronunciation features. Student knows what are the main problems and theoretical viewpoints related to the Estonian phonetics and phonology. Student can describe articulation of sounds and recognize sounds according to the description and classify them according to some articulatory feature. Student can syllabify, identify foot boundaries and word's quantity. Student has elementary knowledge about analyzing speech acoustically (except students of block mode study). Student (except students of Special Eduacation) knows the main rules of the Finno-Ugric phonetic transcription and can use it to transcribe Estonian.
